<p>Insert a C before each capitalized word (except those that begin sentences):</p>
<p>&#8220;The Coptic creed has a chaste charm. It chose, one assumes, not to be clever; it neither cheats the cripple, nor chides the crazed sinner for his crude crime; it is not cold. Then cleave to it; ere thy grave closes, thou mayst find here the chart to the crest thou cravest to climb.&#8221;</p>
